folder: 67th Street (East) & Between Lexington and 3rd Avenues., Manhattan, NY
original_title: Manhattan: 67th Street (East) - Between Lexington and 3rd Avenues.
text:
136 East 57th Street, south side, between Lexington and Third Avenues. The architects for this apartment house were Walker & Gillette.

About 1924.

John Wallace Gillies.
Gift of E.M. Jenks

North on Third Avenue from 67th Street station of Third Avenue 'El'.

March 31, 1928.

P.L. Sperr, photographer.

East 67th Street, north side, West from Third Avenue to Central Park (left).  Prominently shown are Ephraim (erected 1890) at 151-5, No 157-9 that houses Fire Engine No 39, Hook and Ladder No 16 and offices of the Board of Education; the 21st Precinct Police Station at No 153,and the New York Neurological Hospital at No 149-151.  Lexington Avenue appears in the left center and all of the aforementioned structures are east of same.

October, 1938

George D chinn
